# analytics_style_guide.mdc

## Trigger
Any dashboard or visualization generation, modification, or review

## Behavior
When Claude Code generates, modifies, or reviews dashboards and visualizations, it must follow and enforce Flipside's analytics styling conventions and best practices.

### 1. Color Palette Standards

#### Primary Colors
- **Brand Blue**: #0052FF (primary actions, key metrics)
- **Brand Purple**: #7C3AED (secondary metrics, highlights)
- **Success Green**: #10B981 (positive trends, gains)
- **Warning Orange**: #F59E0B (caution, neutral changes)
- **Error Red**: #EF4444 (negative trends, losses)

#### Secondary Colors
- **Gray Scale**: #F9FAFB, #F3F4F6, #E5E7EB, #D1D5DB, #9CA3AF, #6B7280, #374151, #1F2937, #111827
- **Accent Colors**: #06B6D4 (cyan), #8B5CF6 (violet), #EC4899 (pink)

#### Usage Guidelines
- Use primary colors for main data series
- Reserve red/green for clear positive/negative indicators
- Use gray scale for supporting elements and text
- Limit color palette to 5-7 colors maximum per visualization

### 2. Typography Standards

#### Font Hierarchy
- **Headers**: Inter Bold, 24px-32px
- **Subheaders**: Inter Semibold, 18px-24px
- **Body Text**: Inter Regular, 14px-16px
- **Captions**: Inter Regular, 12px-14px
- **Data Labels**: Inter Medium, 12px-14px

#### Text Usage
- Use consistent font weights throughout dashboard
- Maintain proper contrast ratios (4.5:1 minimum)
- Left-align body text, center-align titles
- Use sentence case for labels, title case for headers

### 3. Grid and Layout Standards

#### Grid System
- **Desktop**: 12-column grid with 24px gutters
- **Tablet**: 8-column grid with 16px gutters
- **Mobile**: 4-column grid with 12px gutters

#### Spacing
- **Padding**: 16px, 24px, 32px, 48px
- **Margins**: 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px
- **Component Spacing**: 16px between related elements, 32px between sections

#### Layout Patterns
- Header with navigation (80px height)
- Sidebar navigation (240px width on desktop)
- Main content area with responsive breakpoints
- Footer with consistent height (60px)

### 4. Chart Type Guidelines

#### Time Series Data
- **Line Charts**: For continuous metrics over time
- **Area Charts**: For volume or cumulative metrics
- **Bar Charts**: For discrete time periods or comparisons

#### Comparative Analysis
- **Horizontal Bar Charts**: For ranking or comparison
- **Stacked Charts**: For part-to-whole relationships
- **Grouped Charts**: For side-by-side comparisons

#### Distribution Analysis
- **Histograms**: For data distribution
- **Box Plots**: For statistical summaries
- **Scatter Plots**: For correlation analysis

#### Blockchain-Specific Charts
- **Candlestick Charts**: For price data
- **Waterfall Charts**: For flow analysis
- **Treemaps**: For portfolio composition
- **Heatmaps**: For correlation matrices

### 5. Interactive Elements

#### Hover States
- Subtle elevation with drop shadow
- Color darken by 10% on hover
- Smooth transitions (200ms ease-in-out)

#### Selection States
- Primary color border (2px)
- Background color at 10% opacity
- Clear visual feedback for user actions

#### Loading States
- Skeleton screens for data loading
- Progress indicators for long operations
- Shimmer effects for content placeholders

### 6. Data Formatting Standards

#### Numbers
- **Large Numbers**: Use K, M, B suffixes (e.g., 1.2M, 5.4B)
- **Percentages**: Show 1-2 decimal places (e.g., 12.5%)
- **Currency**: Use appropriate symbols and formatting ($1,234.56)
- **Decimals**: Consistent precision across related metrics

#### Dates and Times
- **Date Format**: MMM DD, YYYY (e.g., Jan 15, 2024)
- **Time Format**: HH:MM AM/PM (e.g., 2:30 PM)
- **Relative Times**: "2 hours ago", "Yesterday", "Last week"

#### Blockchain-Specific Formatting
- **Addresses**: Truncate with ellipsis (0x1234...5678)
- **Transaction Hashes**: Truncate with ellipsis (0xabcd...ef12)
- **Gas Prices**: Use Gwei units with 2 decimal places
- **Block Numbers**: Use comma separators (1,234,567)

### 7. Responsive Design Requirements

#### Breakpoints
- **Mobile**: < 768px
- **Tablet**: 768px - 1024px
- **Desktop**: > 1024px

#### Adaptive Behavior
- Stack charts vertically on mobile
- Simplify navigation on smaller screens
- Adjust font sizes proportionally
- Collapse detailed data into expandable sections

### 8. Accessibility Standards

#### WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance
- Color contrast ratios meet minimum requirements
- All interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Screen reader support with proper ARIA labels
- Alternative text for all visualizations

#### Color Blindness Considerations
- Don't rely solely on color to convey information
- Use patterns, shapes, or labels alongside color
- Test with color blindness simulators
- Provide alternative data representations

### 9. Performance Guidelines

#### Optimization Standards
- Lazy load charts below the fold
- Use efficient data structures and queries
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Minimize bundle sizes with code splitting

#### Loading Performance
- Display skeleton screens within 100ms
- Show meaningful content within 1 second
- Complete page load within 3 seconds
- Provide progress indicators for operations > 2 seconds

### 10. Quality Assurance Checklist

#### Pre-Publication Review
- [ ] Color palette consistency across all charts
- [ ] Typography hierarchy properly implemented
- [ ] Grid alignment and spacing standards met
- [ ] Interactive elements function correctly
- [ ] Data formatting consistent and accurate
- [ ] Responsive design works on all breakpoints
- [ ] Accessibility requirements satisfied
- [ ] Performance benchmarks achieved

#### Common Violations to Flag
- Inconsistent color usage across visualizations
- Poor contrast ratios in text or chart elements
- Misaligned grid elements or inconsistent spacing
- Inappropriate chart types for data being displayed
- Missing or inconsistent data formatting
- Non-responsive design elements
- Accessibility issues with color-only information
- Performance issues with large datasets

### 11. Review and Feedback Process

#### Style Guide Violations
- Flag violations immediately during generation
- Provide specific guidance for corrections
- Suggest alternative approaches that meet standards
- Document common issues for future reference

#### Improvement Suggestions
- Recommend chart type optimizations
- Suggest color palette improvements
- Provide layout enhancement ideas
- Identify accessibility improvements

#### Stakeholder Communication
- Explain style guide rationale to stakeholders
- Provide examples of compliant vs. non-compliant designs
- Educate on best practices for blockchain analytics
- Maintain consistency across team members
